TY  - JOUR
T1  - Organized Dissonance: Feminist Bureaucracy as Hybrid Form
AU  - Ashcraft, Karen Lee
Y1  - 2001/12/01
PY  - 2001
DA  - 2001/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/3069402
DO  - 10.5465/3069402
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 1301
EP  - 1322
VL  - 44
IS  - 6
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Feminist bureaucracy, a response to a historical tension between feminist theorists and practitioners, merges opposed models of power. Through qualitative analysis of power in practice, I examine the novelty and viability of feminist bureaucracy as a distinct hybrid form I term ?organized dissonance.? This form of organization upsets the conventional view that rationality requires resolution, suggesting the potential of strategic incongruity. It also underscores the significance of structure-practice and partner-environment relationships.
AB  - Feminist bureaucracy, a response to a historical tension between feminist theorists and practitioners, merges opposed models of power. Through qualitative analysis of power in practice, I examine the novelty and viability of feminist bureaucracy as a distinct hybrid form I term ?organized dissonance.? This form of organization upsets the conventional view that rationality requires resolution, suggesting the potential of strategic incongruity. It also underscores the significance of structure-practice and partner-environment relationships.
