TY  - JOUR
T1  - Organizations Unfettered: Organizational Form in an Information-Intensive Economy
AU  - Child, John
AU  - McGrath, Rita Gunther
Y1  - 2001/12/01
PY  - 2001
DA  - 2001/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/3069393
DO  - 10.5465/3069393
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 1135
EP  - 1148
VL  - 44
IS  - 6
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The transition from an economy based on materials to an economy based on flows of information has created considerable challenges for organization design by unfettering many organizational aspects from physical constraints. We view the resulting new organizational forms as coping with four core issues: interdependence, disembodiment, velocity, and power. The nine articles in this special research forum provide evidence on how forms have changed, as well as on which aspects of traditional theorizing are likely to continue to be robust. Core themes reflected are an acceptance of contradiction and paradox, a shift in the goal of organizing from buffering against uncertainty to responding to it, a strategic focus on structure and process design, a reemphasis on the social and interpersonal, and a reemergence of issues of legitimacy.
AB  - The transition from an economy based on materials to an economy based on flows of information has created considerable challenges for organization design by unfettering many organizational aspects from physical constraints. We view the resulting new organizational forms as coping with four core issues: interdependence, disembodiment, velocity, and power. The nine articles in this special research forum provide evidence on how forms have changed, as well as on which aspects of traditional theorizing are likely to continue to be robust. Core themes reflected are an acceptance of contradiction and paradox, a shift in the goal of organizing from buffering against uncertainty to responding to it, a strategic focus on structure and process design, a reemphasis on the social and interpersonal, and a reemergence of issues of legitimacy.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/3069393
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/3069393
Y2  - 2026/04/24
